  "texts": [
    "Algorithm auditing (Koshiyama et al., 2021), and specifically AI auditing (Mökander, 2023), is a concept coined to seek for the development of auditing frameworks on research and in practice.",
    "Moving from a case-by-case basis, audits should establish formal assurance that algorithms are legal, ethical, and safe by informing on governance and compliance with regulations and standards.",
    "Notably, the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) of the United Kingdom has developed a such a framework for auditing AI systems in the public and private sectors foot_4.",
    "These investigations assess how these entities process personal information and effectively deal with information rights issues.",
    "In this capacity, an audit will involve a thorough evaluation of an organisation's procedures, processes, records, and activities."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Algorithm auditing (Koshiyama et al., 2021), and specifically AI auditing (Mökander, 2023), is a concept coined to seek for the development of auditing frameworks on research and in practice."
  ]
